Joseph Olaoluwa Air Peace has taken delivery of a new ERJ-145 aircraft to help boost its domestic and regional operations. According to a statement from the firm titled ‘Air Peace takes delivery of another ERJ-145 Aircraft’, dated October 10 and emailed to our correspondent by the firm, the new aircraft, with registration number 5N-BXF arrived the Murtala Muhammed International Airport at about 20:00hrs on Saturday, October 10. Spokesperson of the airline, Stanley Olisa, said the new arrival is a 50-seater aircraft. He said, “We are very glad to announce the arrival of our eighth Embraer 145 Jet, another addition to the fleet of our subsidiary, Air Peace Hopper.” Olisa restated the airline’s commitment to ease the burden of travel in Nigeria and beyond. Air Peace now boasts of 26 aircraft in its fleet, Olisa said. He added, “We’re also gearing up to receive two brand new 124-seat capacity Embraer 195-E2 jets this October, the first set of the 13 we had ordered, with purchase rights for 17 more.” Olisa affirmed Air Peace’s ambition to interconnect various cities in the country. He said the flying public should expect more domestic and international routes including London and Houston to be launched soon. Copyright PUNCH.
